## Installation & Usage

### Install the Cog
```
[p]cog install <your_repo> kickalerts
[p]load kickalerts
```

### Quick Start

```
# Set the default channel for alerts
[p]kickalert setchannel #stream-alerts

# Add a streamer
[p]kickalert add xqc

# Add a streamer with a specific channel
[p]kickalert add ninja #ninja-alerts

# Set a role to ping
[p]kickalert setrole @LiveNotify

# Set a custom message with placeholders
[p]kickalert message xqc ?? {streamer} just went live playing {game}! Go watch: {url}

# Test the embed
[p]kickalert test xqc

# Check current status
[p]kickalert check xqc

# View all settings
[p]kickalert settings
```

---

## Feature Summary

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Multi-streamer support** | Monitor unlimited Kick.com streamers per server |
| **Beautiful embeds** | Detailed or minimal style with thumbnails, viewer counts, categories, tags |
| **Role pinging** | Global or per-streamer role mentions |
| **Custom messages** | Placeholders: `{streamer}`, `{game}`, `{title}`, `{url}`, `{viewers}` |
| **Live updating** | Embeds update with current viewer count while live |
| **Offline handling** | Auto-delete or edit to offline embed when stream ends |
| **Configurable interval** | 30s–600s polling interval |
| **Test command** | Preview embeds even when streamer is offline |
| **Force check** | Manually trigger an immediate check |

---

> **?? Important Notes:**
> - Kick.com's API is **unofficial** and may change without notice. If the API structure changes, the `_parse_stream_info` method will need updating.
> - The minimum polling interval is 30 seconds to avoid potential rate limiting from Kick's servers.
> - Make sure the bot has `Send Messages`, `Embed Links`, and `Mention Roles` permissions in the alert channels.
